EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 222300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING LOW CENTRED FORTIES 998 WILL DOMINATE CONDITIONS ACROSS
CULLERCOATS WITH A TROUGH EXTENDING SE INTO CONTINENTAL EUROPE. THE AZORES
HIGH PRESSURE WILL ALSO EXTEND A RIDGE N W OF THE UK AND TOWARDS ICELAND.
THROUGH TUESDAY THIS LOW CENTRE VERY SLWY MOVS E AND FILLS TO BE CENTRED
FISHER 1002 BEFORE THEN CONTINUING E INTO SCANDINAVIA THROUGH WEDNESDAY.
A WEAK RIDGE THEN FOLLOWS ACROSS THE UK WITH HIGH PRESSURE BLDN E OF ICELAND
AND ALSO AMPLIFYING N FM IBERIA. SHALLOW LOW DEVELOPING SO THE SW OF THE
UK THEN BECOMES STNR AS PRESSURE BUILDS ACROSS THE UK AND EERN CULLERCOATS
ON THURSDAY. SHALLOW LOW PRESSURE PERSISTS SKAGERRAK. GALES ARE NOT EXP THROUGH
THE PERIOD HOWEVER STRG WINDS ARE POSS NEAR LOW CENTRE ON MONDAY EVENING.
FURTHER STRG WINDS POSS ACROSS N AND W CULLERCOATS FOR A TIME EARLY WEDNESDAY
AND EERN CULLERCOATS THURSDAY
